sections.text:
class Parent:
    pass

class Child(Parent):
    pass

Child inherits all attributes and methods from Parent

Child class can override parent method:

class Animal:
    def speak(self):
        pass

class Dog(Animal):
    def speak(self):
        return 'Woof!'

Different classes can have method with same name:

for animal in [Dog(), Cat()]:
    print(animal.speak())

en.codeExample:
class Animal:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name

    def speak(self):
        return '...'

class Dog(Animal):
    def speak(self):
        return f'{self.name} says: Woof!'

class Cat(Animal):
    def speak(self):
        return f'{self.name} says: Meow!'

# Polymorphism
animals = [Dog('Bobik'), Cat('Murzik')]
for animal in animals:
    print(animal.speak())

# Type check
print(isinstance(Dog('Test'), Animal))  # True

